typeProperties.script:
source(output(
		Empid as string,
		Name as string,
		Country as string,
		Department as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> source1
source1 aggregate(groupBy(Department),
	Employeecount = count(Empid)) ~> Aggregate1
Aggregate1 sink(input(
		{30} as string,
		Rahul as string,
		India as string,
		{33} as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	partitionFileNames:['aggregatefile.csv'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> sink1

source(output(
		Column_1 as string,
		Column_2 as string,
		Column_3 as integer '000',
		Column_4 as string,
		Column_5 as integer '000'
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> source22
source(output(
		Column_1 as string,
		Column_2 as string,
		Column_3 as string,
		Column_4 as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> source2
source22 aggregate(Column_3 = sum(Column_3),
		Column_5 = count(Column_5)) ~> Aggregate1
source22, Aggregate1 union(byName: true,
	partitionBy('roundRobin', 2))~> Union1
Union1 sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> sink1

source(output(
		empid as string,
		name as string,
		country as string,
		department as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> source1
source1 filter(equals(department, '3')) ~> Filter1
Filter1 sink(input(
		Column_1 as string,
		Column_2 as string,
		Column_3 as string,
		Column_4 as string,
		Column_5 as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	partitionFileNames:['filter.csv'],
	truncate: true,
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> sink1

source(output(
		Empid as string,
		Name as string,
		Country as string,
		Department as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> Employeesdata
Employeesdata split(equals(Department, '1'),
	equals(Department, '2'),
	equals(Department, '3'),
	disjoint: false) ~> ConditionalSplit1@(ITEmployees, HREmployees, PayrollEmployees, OtherEmployees)
ConditionalSplit1@ITEmployees sink(input(
		{30} as string,
		Rahul as string,
		India as string,
		{33} as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	partitionFileNames:['conditiona.csv'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> sink1
ConditionalSplit1@HREmployees sink(input(
		{30} as string,
		Rahul as string,
		India as string,
		{33} as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	partitionFileNames:['hremployees.csv'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> sink2

source(output(
		empid as string,
		name as string,
		country as string,
		department as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> Employees
source(output(
		Depid as string,
		Depname as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> Departments
Employees, Departments join(department == Depid,
	joinType:'inner',
	broadcast: 'auto')~> Join1
Join1 sink(allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	partitionFileNames:['hari.csv'],
	mapColumn(
		empid,
		name,
		country,
		Depid,
		Depname
	),
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> sink1

source(output(
		Empid as string,
		Name as string,
		Country as string,
		Department as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	ignoreNoFilesFound: false) ~> source1
source1 split(equals(Department, '1'),
	equals(Department, '2'),
	equals(Department, '3'),
	disjoint: false) ~> ConditionalSplit1@(ITemployees, HREmployees, PayrollEmployees, Others)
ConditionalSplit1@ITemployees sink(input(
		Department as string,
		Employeecount as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	partitionFileNames:['harishITempl.csv'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> sink1
ConditionalSplit1@HREmployees sink(input(
		Department as string,
		Employeecount as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	partitionFileNames:['harishHRempl.csv'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> sink2
ConditionalSplit1@PayrollEmployees sink(input(
		Department as string,
		Employeecount as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	partitionFileNames:['harishpayrollempl.csv'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> sink3
ConditionalSplit1@Others sink(input(
		Department as string,
		Employeecount as string
	),
	allowSchemaDrift: true,
	validateSchema: false,
	partitionFileNames:['harishothers.csv'],
	partitionBy('hash', 1),
	skipDuplicateMapInputs: true,
	skipDuplicateMapOutputs: true) ~> sink4
